Harry Redknapp has revealed he was attacked with coins and verbally abused by Arsenal fans as he left the Emirates Stadium after the Gunners ' 4-1 win over Liverpool .
Currently out of work after leaving his position at Queens Park Rangers , the former Tottenham boss was at the Emirates as a spectator on April 4 when some fans turned against him .
Redkn was claims he had earlier signed autographs and posed for pictures with supporters , but a group of supporters began abusing him .